node.text:
If we can make these so can you 🤩 y’all these were actually so much easier to make than I thought! Fun activity to do with the fam for sure! 

Tips I learned: 
-fill in any thin spots to avoid breaking
-the white chocolate is a lot sturdier and easier to remove from molds
-ornament molds worked SO much better than ice silicone molds 👍🏻

node.text: I miss clay popping videos! I only ever posted 1 on here and it was a whole year ago! I got a lot of comments from people that arnt in the slime community asking what these were and how to make them. These are creations made out of clay that you cover in nail polish and they crack when you squish them 😍 in this video I show you how and what I use to make them!

node.text: I know I’m late but Happy Father’s Day! ✨FUN FACT: Raul always gave me Dad vibes. For years I’ve always told him he was such a Dad. Idk how to explain it.. his cheesy jokes, how kids love him, how nurturing he is.. I just knew he’d be the best Dad one day. And that day is now. Thank you for being the most amazing father and husband. I love u squish 🥲❤️

node.text:
For this Child I have prayed and the Lord has granted the desires of my Heart 🕊 - 1 Samuel 1:27 

Mia Violeta 
April 19, 2021🤍12:34am
9lbs 3oz, 20in.

Welcome to the world my sweet angel baby 👼🏻

Full labor and delivery video is now up 🥲

node.text:
April 19, 2021🤍
The day God made me a Mother. I’m still in disbelief. This all feels like a dream.. Every second of my 34hr labor and even up to pushing.. EVERY SINGLE SECOND up until she was finally out breathing and crying, I would question if something could go wrong because I simply could not believe it was finally happening for us. After nearly 3 hours of pushing, I gave birth to a big beautiful healthy baby girl. I’m in complete bliss.. I’m so in love. MY HEART IS SO FULL.

node.text: Dreamt and prayed for this moment. IT’S TIME!!!
